</body></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarantrunemaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arant Runemaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/15/01 12:55:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Potions?</span><hr size=1> I got lucky- some crazy person was actually CAMPING the mobs down under lake rathe- so wen I went to grab the rod they were all dead- as to the da*n Lguk rod- I died twice (did this 39 I think? Thats when I did all the easy wiz quests: acumen/runscale/etc) Anyway- I just looked at maps and CAREFULLY (as the vampire bats see invis) get to the frezny room(actually I got rezzed in, wansnt the best rod for me)- I waited there while the group killed hand, then I just went in and grabbed it. First time I went in alone and hand just slaughtered me, because I forgot it saw my ivu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/15/01 1:29:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Potions?</span><hr size=1> You can purchase ITU potions from your neighborhood shaman (fairly expensive and just as unreliable as invis.)  It really sucks when you quaff a 15pp potion only to have the affect wear off immediatly.<br>
<br>
As far as the enduring breath potions go you cna buy those in Felwythe from the small shop outside the casters guilds.<br>
<br>
They run about 10pp each and last quite a while (easier that finding a Shaman with fish scales).  <br>
<br>
As far as the goblins go just swim in and make sure to con everything before you aproach the tower.  <br>
<br>
If anything scowles at you you can either sacrafice yourself (because you will not make it out of there) and grab the rod or find a group. <p><P></P>
