Thanks for all the advice, y'all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udanenel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/01 8:20:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Last two Staff of the Wheel pieces ...</span><hr size=1> Ok my 2 cents. I did this quest at level 22. <br>
<br>
For the Lake Rathe piece, you need something to give you extra breath. What I did was I gated to WC, ran to the EC tunnel and pleaded for some help. A High level shaman cast SOW and Enduring Breath on me. I said thanks and immediately gated to NK. I then ran through SK, cast lev and ran out to the island. I was easily able to swim in and collect the rod and gate out. Piece of cake.<br>
<br>
For the LGuk rod, this was also very easy but it took the longest time. I got to the Lower Guk Dead side near the waterfall there. I then bound myself right there. I would return often and ask if the Hands room was cleared. After 4 or 5 days of doing this (believe it was a friday evening) sure enough, the room was cleared out. I then did an /ooc and asked for help from a high level ENC. One responded and came over and gave me ITU and led me to the hands room. I grabbed the rod and gated.<br>
<br>
I know people who have done this quest as early as level 16 with help. It's a fun quest and a great staff.<br>
